# The ledger is append-only JSONL — two branches that both append lines are never a
# real conflict, but the default 3-way merge can still resolve the file to only one side's
# committed tree (an approve-merge can check out over minutes of live in-flight ops appends).
# git's built-in `union` driver instead takes lines from both sides. Pairs with the
# id-dedupe-on-read in ledger.ts's loadAllEvents (belt-and-suspenders for a union merge
# echoing one line into both hunks).
.ai/ledger/*.jsonl merge=union
